message.content: One of the most significant events that happened in the Dominican Republic in the past 100 years is the assassination of the dictator Rafael Trujillo on May 30, 1961. Trujillo ruled the country for over three decades with an iron fist, and his assassination marked the end of his brutal regime. The event had a profound impact on the country, leading to a period of political instability followed by democratic reforms. It is considered a pivotal moment in the modern history of the Dominican Republic.
